    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a collector-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant. This specimen retains its factory-correct vacuum line topography and untouched ECU, ensuring the complex primary-to-secondary boost transition remains linear and responsive. The chassis architecture provides a perfect 50/50 weight distribution, complemented by an unmolested aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. The undercarriage is free of oxidation, and the apex seals show excellent compression across all faces. An investment-grade example for the discerning enthusiast who demands mechanical purity.",
