      "description": "Available is an impeccably maintained 997.1 Carrera S, a definitive analog experience for the discerning driver. This specimen features the 3.8L naturally aspirated flat-six powerplant, producing 355hp and 295 lb-ft of torque, mated to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The mechanical suite includes Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) with a lowered ride height and a factory-spec limited-slip differential for optimal lateral weight transfer and traction. The braking system utilizes four-piston aluminum monobloc fixed calipers and cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of thermal stress. With a documented service history confirming the integrity of the IMS bearing and rear main seal, this chassis remains rigid and communicative, free of any bushing deflection or drivetrain lash. Truly a turn-key, investment-grade vehicle.",
